cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CL. 

The paper deals with temporal action localization in videos, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new approach that involves adding constraints to the curves that predict the probabilities of action starts, continues, and ends, which is a machine learning technique. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), or cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on two popular datasets, THUMOS14 and ActivityNet1.3, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
